### Non-message mediums

Do not change your avatar, nickname, username or custom/rich status to try to protest a moderation action, or to attack
any user.

#### Nicknames

All nicknames must adhere to the rules above. Additionally, they should not be hard to read or too noisy. Nicknames
may be considered difficult to read or noisy if they contain emojis, Zalgo or other difficult-to-read styling, or
Unicode control characters. "Empty" nicknames are also considered difficult to read.

#### Avatars

All avatars must adhere to the rules above. Additionally, avatars depicting objectionable or NSFW (Not Safe For Work)
content are disallowed, as well as avatars that appear to be "blank" by blending in with the background of the Discord
client.

#### Custom/Rich Statuses

All user statuses must adhere to the rules above. In particular, we don't want to see objectionable or NSFW custom
emoji, advertising sketchy or NSFW websites, or hateful sentiment.

### Reporting

To report rule-breaking behaviour in public, mention the **@Modertater**{ .has-text-modertater } role directly in the
channel, and a staff member will be along as soon as they can be. Alternatively, you can send a private message
directly to any staff member.

If your report concerns a member of staff, please send a private message directly to **a different member of staff**.
All private reports will be treated with confidentiality.
    {% endcolumn %}
    {% column "is-half" %}
### Enforcement

Our staff team have multiple tools at their disposal when dealing with rule-breakers, including the following:

* Verbally/textually warning or correcting users
* Forcibly changing a user's nickname
* Temporarily muting users
* Temporarily or permanently removing users from the community (kicking, tempbanning, banning)

Each situation is unique, and will be assessed on a case-by-case basis. All actions taken in response to rule-breaking
behaviour is done at the discretion of the moderator in question - however, we will take feedback from community members
if they're not happy with how things were resolved.

We do not currently have a way to appeal community bans. While we're figuring that out, feel free to add `gdude#2002` as
a friend and send your appeal in a private message.

#### Moderation Guidelines

Moderation is a complicated subject at best, and it requires a lot of nuance and difficult decision-making. While
it's impossible to enumerate every possible situation (and some situations will not suit our documentation), we've done
our best to explain how we come to a decision, and what we expect from our staff team.

For more information on this, feel free to read
[our moderation guidelines](/community/moderation). If you have any feedback on this document, feel free to contact us!
    {% endcolumn %}
{% endcolumns %}
